<Base title="Headless E-Commerce" description="Headless E-Commerce for more freedom of decision in your core business – Shopware 6 by Hob by Horse.">
<div class="lp"><section class="hero"><div class="hi">
<p class="kicker">E-Commerce</p>
<h1>Headless E-Commerce for More Freedom of Decision in Your Core Business</h1>
<p>With the Headless E-Commerce feature of Shopware 6, you give your target group completely independent shopping experiences across the widest variety of sales channels. This creates growth potential for online shops with no upper limits.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Headless E-Commerce in Development by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>In conventional e-commerce, backend and frontend are inseparably linked. Through the headless e-commerce solution, frontend and backend are decoupled in Shopware 6. Changes in the frontend do not affect the bundled business processes in the backend. You therefore still have full access to all known, existing functionalities. This innovation represents an enormous time saving when integrating and testing new interfaces, connections and touchpoints.</p>

<h2>Contents of Headless E-Commerce with Shopware 6</h2>
<p>These changes compared to conventional e-commerce can be added to your online shop by Hob by Horse:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>API-first headless architecture:</strong> You are independent of providers. You can integrate components into your business model at any time when market trends change.</li>
<li><strong>Headless e-commerce solution:</strong> Frontend and backend are decoupled from each other. While your target group shops undisturbed on sales channels, you can reduce performance losses on both sides through individual scaling.</li>
<li><strong>Headless CMS:</strong> For individual shop pages or discount campaigns without administrative adjustments.</li>
<li><strong>Touchpoints of the customer journey:</strong> You can integrate various sales channels for a perceptible build-up of your corporate image.</li>
</ul>
<p>Further contents of this concept include features for storytelling, virtual showrooms, filter functions, seamless social shopping integration and product configurations.</p>

<h2>Industries that Benefit from Headless E-Commerce</h2>
<p>The larger the online shop, the stronger the impact of the innovations of headless e-commerce on your customer appeal and brand development. Industry examples include the cosmetics and beauty industry, the manufacturing sector in the automotive and tool industries, or all small online shops and large corporations in the lifestyle industry.</p>

<h2>Benefits of Headless E-Commerce Developments by Hob by Horse for Your Target Groups</h2>
<p>B2B target groups are specialist customers who want to see, take and go immediately. Advice must therefore be available in real time, while on the other side you are adapting the online shop for the next update. B2C target groups are equally impatient. Such technical details must not under any circumstances disrupt the virtual shopping experience.</p>
<p>Would you like to learn more details about headless e-commerce or immediately position your online shop with this component quickly on the market? Call us or describe your question to Hob by Horse in an email!</p>
</div></div>
</Base>
